	<TD WIDTH="20%"><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000">Author</FONT></TD>
	<TD><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="2"COLOR="#000000">Guild professionals</FONT></TD>
</TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cdcdcd" ALIGN="LEFT">
<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="sans-serif" COLOR="#000000"><b>Rohwin</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000"><B></B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">Joined: Jun 03, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">Posts: 93</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">From: Freeport<br></FONT></td><TD><img src="/forums/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">Posted: 2002-04-15 17:22&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#000000" face="sans-serif">Greetings,<BR><BR>The House of Lords has passed new rules regarding guild professionals. These professionals are the members who wish to offer their services of the many tradeskills available in Everquest.<BR><BR>Anyone who wishes to become a guild professional may declare their intent. The catagories available will be each of the trade skills that exist in Everquest, plus an extra catagory for a guild merchant. A forum catagory called "The Marketplace" has been created for people to advertise their skills and take orders.<BR><BR>Just by offering your services to the guild you will become an apprentice of your trade skill. When a tradeskill professional performs a service for a guild member, and that guild member is fully satisfied with the results, then we will ask that the member receiving the service offer a praise of the profesional's performance. Once an apprentice's skill reaches 100 or higher and they have recieved praise from 3 different guild members, then they will be considered a journeyman and earn 1 political point. Since there is no skill for a guild merchant, a member will only need to be praised by 3 members. If the professional's skill reaches 175 or higher and they have received praise from 5 different members, then they will earn an additional political point and the title of master. There is no way to verify what someone's trade skill actually is, however, I think we can rely on the honor system here. A maximum of 5 points may be earned through trade skills, but there are no limit to the number of titles one may possess.<BR><BR>Guild professionals will not be obligated to perform any duties for the guild nor are discounts required. All that we ask of them is that they offer a fair deal to our members, but the specifics of the deal are strictly between the professional and the member who wishes to use their services.<BR><BR>Fare thee well everyone,<BR><BR>
<BR>_________________<BR><img src="/images/rohwinssymbol.gif" width=60 height=42 align=left valign=center alt="Rohwin's Vanguard">Rohwin Amoure Ardour<BR>Regent of Cursus Honorum</FONT><BR>
